---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer and Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="Legal disclaimers, affiliate disclosure, and terms of use for Section 75 Claim Helper."
>
  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

    <h1>Disclaimer and affiliate disclosure</h1>

    <h2>General information only</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>This website provides general information and templates. It is not legal advice.</strong>
    </p>

    <p>
      The content on this website does not constitute legal advice for your specific situation. Section 75 claims depend on the individual facts of each case, the terms of your credit agreement, the nature of your purchase, and other factors that vary from person to person.
    </p>

    <p>
      Nothing on this site should be relied upon as a substitute for advice from a qualified solicitor. If you are uncertain about your legal position, or if the amount at stake is significant, we recommend consulting a consumer law solicitor before proceeding.
    </p>

    <h2>Not a claims management company</h2>

    <p>
      We are not a claims management company. We do not handle claims, contact banks, negotiate with card providers, or represent customers. We provide general information and downloadable template documents only.
    </p>

    <p>
      Nothing on this site creates a client relationship between you and this website, or any obligation on our part to act on your behalf in any dispute.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you are approached by a company offering to handle your Section 75 claim in exchange for a fee or a percentage of the refund, check that they are authorised by the Financial Conduct Authority before engaging them. You can search the FCA register at <a href="https://register.fca.org.uk">register.fca.org.uk</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Accuracy of information</h2>

    <p>
      We take care to ensure the information on this site is accurate and up to date. However, the law can change, and Financial Ombudsman Service decisions evolve over time. We cannot guarantee that every article reflects the current state of the law at the time you read it.
    </p>

    <p>
      Primary sources, including the Consumer Credit Act 1974 and FOS decisions, should be consulted directly where they are material to your decision. Links to primary sources are provided throughout this site where relevant.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>

    <p>
      Some pages on this site contain affiliate links to credit card and financial products. If you apply for a product via one of these links, we may receive a commission from the product provider. This is disclosed clearly at the top of any page where affiliate links appear.
    </p>

    <p>
      Our affiliate relationships do not influence which products we feature or the order in which we present them. We recommend products on the basis of their suitability for consumers making Section 75 claims, their customer service track record, and their terms and conditions. Commission rates are not a factor in our recommendations.
    </p>

    <p>
      We comply with the ASA CAP Code on affiliate disclosure. If you have a concern about a specific affiliate link or recommendation on this site, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>

    <p>
      This site links to external websites including legislation.gov.uk, the Financial Ombudsman Service, and the Insolvency Service. We are not responsible for the content of external sites and cannot guarantee their accuracy or availability.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>

    <p>
      We collect only the information you voluntarily provide via the contact form on this site: your name, email address, and message. This information is used solely to respond to your enquiry and is not shared with third parties, used for marketing, or stored beyond what is necessary to handle your message.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not use tracking cookies or third-party advertising technology. Anonymous, aggregate traffic statistics may be collected to understand how pages are used; no personally identifiable information is captured in this process.
    </p>
    <p>
      You have the right to request deletion of any personal data we hold. To do so, contact us via the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
    </p>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
